<ul><li>public accommodations</li><br />
<li>employment</li><br />
<li>transportation</li><br />
<li>state and local government services</li><br />
<li>telecommunications</li><br />
</ul><p>The U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ) <a href=""http://www.justice.gov/crt/about/drs/"">Disability Rights Section</a> provides information about the ADA through a toll-free information line: 1-800-514-0301/TTY: 1-800-514-0383. This service permits businesses, state and local governments, and individuals to call and ask questions about general or specific ADA requirements and regulations, including questions about the <a href=""http://www.ada.gov/2010ADAstandards_index.htm"">ADA Standards for Accessible Design</a>.<br /> </p><br />
