"Order of Presidential Succession","Information on order of presidential succession.","<p>The U.S. Constitution and the <a href=""https://www.senate.gov/artandhistory/history/minute/Presidential_Succession_Act.htm"">Presidential Succession Act of 1947</a> give guidelines for the presidential order of succession.</p><br />
<p>If the President of the United States is incapacitated, dies, resigns, is for any reason unable to hold his/her office, or is removed from office, he/she will be replaced in the following order:</p><br />
