<li>Pennsylvania</li><br />
<li>Rhode Island</li><br />
<li>Vermont</li><br />
<li>Washington</li><br />
</ol><p>The <a href=""http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/bdquery/z?d104:H.R.3396:"">Defense of Marriage Act (DOMA)</a> allows states to refuse to recognize same-sex marriages performed in other states.</p><br />
<p>Same-sex couples may be eligible for certain rights and benefits similar to, or the same as, those under marriage through state civil union or domestic partnership laws. For information on these laws, please consult with your state government or with a licensed attorney.</p><br />
