"Pay Scales and Benefits for Congress and Federal Employees","Information on pay scales and benefits for Congress and federal employees. ","<p>All federal employees hired after 1983 <a href=""http://www.ssa.gov/retire2/fedgovees.htm"">pay Social Security taxes</a>, including the President, the Vice President, members of Congress, sitting federal judges, certain legislative branch employees, and most political appointees. The government collects these taxes in the same amounts as they would if these employees worked in the private sector at the same salary level.</p><br />
