</ul><h3>Combine Military Service and Civil Service Retirement</h3><br />
<p>Military service does not automatically count toward civil service retirement, but you can <a href=""http://www.opm.gov/retirement-services/fers-information/military-retired-pay/"">buy into (buy back) the civil service retirement fund</a> for military service performed after 1956. A few items that you should take into consideration: the date you came under the civil service system and whether or not you are eligible for Social Security.</p><br />
