"Electric Power Grids","Learn how the power grid supplies electricity to consumers","<p>An <a href=""http://www.eia.gov/energy_in_brief/article/power_grid.cfm"">electric power grid</a> is a network of transmission and distribution lines that carries electricity from plants to consumers. The United States does not have a national power grid.</p><br />
<p>View some <a href=""http://energy.gov/oe/technology-development/smart-grid/interactive-grid""> interactive animations</a> to learn about electricity generation, transmission, and distribution, and see how various factors affect the reliability and pricing of electricity.</p><br />
<h3>Smart Grid</h3><br />
