"Automated Export System (AES) – Formerly Shipper Export Declaration (SED)","Electronic Export Information for shipments over $2,500.","<h3>What is AES/SED and why do I need to file one?</h3><br />
<p>All export shipments over $2,500 must file Electronic Export Information or EEI.</p><br />
<p>The electronic system used to file EEI is called AES, which stands for Automated Export System. You can find a short <a href=""http://www.export.gov/logistics/aes/"">video explaining EEI and the AES</a> by visiting <a href=""http://www.export.gov/"">Export.gov</a>. Select the Solutions tab, then <a href=""http://www.export.gov/logistics/"">International Logistics</a>, and then the <a href=""http://www.export.gov/logistics/aes/"">Automated Export System</a> link under Related Topics.</p><br />
<p>You can find information about, and access, AES at <a href=""http://aesdirect.census.gov/"">http://aesdirect.census.gov/</a>. On this website, you will find information on how to:</p><br />
<ul><li>Register a new account;</li><br />
<li>Manage your account;</li><br />
<li>Get training about AES;</li><br />
<li>Access help resources and other information about AES online platforms such as AESPcLink and AESDirect VPN.</li><br />
</ul><p>If you have additional questions or issues with the AES, please speak with a specialist at the Census Bureau’s Foreign Trade Division AES. Please call 1-800-549-0595 and select option 1.</p><br />
